{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"921e735e-cd48-442a-a9fe-f369830f59d6","content":"The tutorial you found is likely based on **Xamarin.Forms** or early MAUI guidance — here's how it works in .NET MAUI (.NET 10):\n\n### `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` — **Not needed**\nIn .NET MAUI, pages **respect the safe area by default** on iOS. Content automatically avoids the notch, status bar, and home indicator. You don't need to opt in with a platform-specific property.\n\n### `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` — **Correct**\nThis is the right property to use on a layout (like a `Grid`) when you want content (e.g., a background image) to extend *behind* the notch/status bar into the unsafe area. Example:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\">\n    <Grid IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\">\n        <!-- Background image fills entire screen including behind notch -->\n        <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n\n        <!-- UI content stays in safe area via padding/layout -->\n        <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20,60,20,20\">\n            <Label Text=\"Hello, World!\" />\n        </VerticalStackLayout>\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n### TL;DR\n| Property | Status in .NET MAUI |\n|---|---|\n| `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` | Unnecessary — safe area is respected by default |\n| `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on layouts | ✅ Correct — use to bleed content into unsafe areas |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"19daed15-4e35-48d3-a49b-d1360f5944de","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - a platform-specific property for ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - on a Grid for background images\n\nLet me think about what I know about .NET MAUI safe area APIs:\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the iOS safe area handling has evolved. Let me search for current information about these APIs.\n\nActually, I should be careful here. Let me think about what I know:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` - This was a Xamarin.Forms platform-specific API. \n\nIn .NET MAUI, the approach shifted significantly—MAUI now respects safe areas on iOS by default, and the old Xamarin.Forms platform-specific property isn't the primary way to control this anymore. Instead, `IgnoreSafeArea` is the property you'd use on layouts to opt out of safe area consideration, which is useful for background images that should extend edge-to-edge. I should be cautious about the exact API surface here since this is a specific technical detail that could have changed between MAUI versions.","outputTokens":1098},"id":"ba1342a5-1def-4d31-8de9-e98551c624fa","timestamp":"2026-04-09T15:29:27.884Z","parentId":"2cf29e75-e4d0-4809-9571-42a6cf0a6fe2"}
